.TH "CSSPOSITIONTRYRULE.STYLE" "3JS" "November 25, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
CSSPositionTryRule.style \- CSSPositionTryRule: style property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The read\-only \f[B]\f[CB]style\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]CSSPositionTryRule\f[R] interface contains a
\f[CR]CSSPositionTryDescriptors\f[R] object representing the descriptors
available in the \f[CR]\(atposition\-try\f[R] rule\(cqs body.
.SH VALUE
A \f[CR]CSSPositionTryDescriptors\f[R] object.
.PP
Although the \f[CR]style\f[R] property itself is read\-only in the sense
that you can\(cqt replace the \f[CR]CSSPositionTryDescriptors\f[R]
object, you can still assign to the \f[CR]style\f[R] property directly,
which is equivalent to assigning to its \f[CR]cssText\f[R] property.
You can also modify the \f[CR]CSSPositionTryDescriptors\f[R] object
using the \f[CR]setProperty()\f[R] and \f[CR]removeProperty()\f[R]
methods.
.SH EXAMPLES
The CSS includes a \f[CR]\(atposition\-try\f[R] at\-rule with a name of
\f[CR]\-\-custom\-right\f[R] and three descriptors.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]\(atposition\-try\f[R] \-\-custom\-bottom {
  top\f[BI]:\f[R] anchor\f[BI](\f[R]bottom\f[BI])\f[R];
  min\-width\f[BI]:\f[R] 100px;
  margin\-top\f[BI]:\f[R] 10px;
}
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] myRules = document.styleSheets[0].cssRules;
\f[B]const\f[R] tryOption = myRules[0]; \f[I]// a CSSPositionTryRule\f[R]
console.log(tryOption.style.top); \f[I]// \(dqanchor(bottom)\(dq\f[R]
console.log(tryOption.style[\(dqmin\-width\(dq]); \f[I]// \(dq100px\(dq\f[R]
console.log(tryOption.style.positionArea); \f[I]// \(dq\(dq; no position\-area specified\f[R]
.EE
